<html lang='en'>
  <head>
    <meta charset='UTF-8' />
    <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0' />
    <title>Non-Compete Agreement</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #333;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
      }
      .header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #333;
        padding-bottom: 10px;
      }
      .header h1 { margin: 0; color: #2c3e50; }
      .section { margin-bottom: 20px; }
      .section-title {
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #2c3e50;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        font-size: 1.1em;
      }
      .signature-block {
        margin-top: 50px;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
      }
      .signature { width: 45%; }
      .signature-line {
        border-top: 1px solid #333;
        margin-top: 40px;
        padding-top: 5px;
      }
      .footer {
        margin-top: 50px;
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 0.9em;
        color: #666;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class='header'>
      <h1>NON-COMPETE AGREEMENT</h1>
      <p>Between {{employerName}} and {{employeeName}}</p>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>CONTRACT REFERENCE</div>
      <p>Contract ID: {{contractId}}</p>
      <p>Date of Issue: {{issueDate}}</p>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>1. PARTIES</div>
      <p><strong>Employer:</strong>
        {{employerName}}<br />
        Address: {{employerAddress}}<br />
        Email: {{employerEmail}}</p>
      <p><strong>Employee:</strong>
        {{employeeName}}<br />
        Address: {{employeeAddress}}<br />
        Email: {{employeeEmail}}</p>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>2. BACKGROUND</div>
      <p>The Employee will be engaged as <strong>{{jobTitle}}</strong> commencing
        <strong>{{startDate}}</strong>. In the course of employment, the Employee
        will gain access to confidential information, trade secrets, client
        relationships, and specialised knowledge that are proprietary to the Employer.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>3. NON-COMPETE RESTRICTION</div>
      <p>During the term of employment and for a period of
        <strong>twelve (12) months</strong> following termination of employment
        (for any reason), the Employee shall not, directly or indirectly:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Be employed by, consult for, or have a financial interest in any business
          that directly competes with the Employer's business</li>
        <li>Solicit, divert, or attempt to divert any client or customer of the Employer</li>
        <li>Solicit or induce any employee of the Employer to leave their employment</li>
        <li>Establish or participate in a competing business in the same industry sector</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>4. GEOGRAPHIC SCOPE</div>
      <p>The restrictions in Section 3 apply within the Federal Republic of Nigeria
        and any other territory in which the Employer actively conducts business
        at the time of the Employee's departure.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>5. PERMITTED ACTIVITIES</div>
      <p>Nothing in this Agreement prevents the Employee from:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Working in a non-competing industry or role</li>
        <li>Engaging in activities that do not harm the Employer's legitimate business interests</li>
        <li>Owning less than 2% of publicly traded shares in a competing company</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>6. CONSIDERATION</div>
      <p>The Employee acknowledges that employment with the Employer, access to
        confidential information, training, and remuneration constitute adequate
        consideration for entering into this Agreement.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>7. SEVERABILITY</div>
      <p>If any provision of this Agreement is found unenforceable, a court may
        modify such provision to the minimum extent necessary to make it
        enforceable. All other provisions remain in full effect.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>8. REMEDIES</div>
      <p>The Employee acknowledges that a breach of this Agreement would cause
        irreparable harm. The Employer is entitled to seek injunctive relief,
        damages, and any other remedies available at law.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='section'>
      <div class='section-title'>9. GOVERNING LAW</div>
      <p>This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the Federal Republic
        of Nigeria.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='signature-block'>
      <div class='signature'>
        <div class='signature-line'>
          <strong>Employer Signature</strong><br />
          Name: {{employerName}}<br />
          {{#if employerSignedAt}}
            Date: {{employerSignedAt}}<br />
            IP: {{employerSignatureIp}}
          {{else}}
            Date: _________________
          {{/if}}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class='signature'>
        <div class='signature-line'>
          <strong>Employee Signature</strong><br />
          Name: {{employeeName}}<br />
          {{#if employeeSignedAt}}
            Date: {{employeeSignedAt}}<br />
            IP: {{employeeSignatureIp}}
          {{else}}
            Date: _________________
          {{/if}}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='footer'>
      <p>Contract processed through JobStack Talent Solutions</p>
      <p>This is a legally binding document. Please read carefully before signing.</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
